content: <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?> <metadata xml:lang="en"> <Esri> <CreaDate>20140925</CreaDate> <CreaTime>13121000</CreaTime> <ArcGISFormat>1.0</ArcGISFormat> <SyncOnce>TRUE</SyncOnce> </Esri> <dataIdInfo> <idAbs>Automatic Identification Systems (AIS) are a navigation safety device that transmits and monitors the location and characteristics of many vessels in U.S. and international waters in real-time. This map service represents the density of all tug and towing vessel traffic in 2011 for the US East and West Coast from tug and towing vessels with AIS transponders in 100 meter grid cells. The data are best interpreted using a high to low density scale and does not represent actual vessel counts.</idAbs> <searchKeys> <keyword>vessel traffic</keyword> <keyword>ship traffic</keyword> <keyword>vessel density</keyword> <keyword>AIS</keyword> <keyword>oceans</keyword> <keyword>tug</keyword> <keyword>tow</keyword> <keyword>towing</keyword> </searchKeys> <idPurp>Density data for tug and towing vessels equipped with AIS transponders during the year 2011.</idPurp> <idCredit>MarineCadastre.gov</idCredit> <resConst> <Consts> <useLimit>These data are intended for coastal and ocean use planning, and are not intended for navigation.</useLimit> </Consts> </resConst> <idCitation> <resTitle>2011 Tug and Towing Vessel Density</resTitle> </idCitation> </dataIdInfo> <Binary> <Thumbnail> <Data EsriPropertyType="PictureX"></Data> </Thumbnail> </Binary> </metadata>
